{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"971ae513-4b03-4d32-908b-f35d4eb5f6c5","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the VSTest compatibility layer is disabled by default.**\n\nMSTest.Sdk 4.x sets `<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>` by default, meaning `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to the new test runner** (recommended):\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n   With the Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` uses the new built-in runner — no VSTest adapter needed.\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** if you must keep `vstest.console`:\n   Add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nOption 1 is the intended path forward. The VSTest bridge is kept only for backward compatibility and may be removed in a future release.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"994e31a6-9d0d-4bba-8d23-c327a0662969","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"083B:204131:8BB8161:9AC16F2:69EAD7B0"},"id":"18bf7d1b-d106-42c1-abe6-7424598af54d","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:38:49.449Z","parentId":"3c508f1b-5e90-42ad-a405-4c11516bec6a"}
